main event: An unidentified object was observed falling towards the earth, burning bright blue and white and giving off red sparks, near Lakenheath, England.
interesting points: The object was observed by an AWS (Air Weather Service) observer.
The object was falling from west to east, approximately 23-25 miles away.
The object was burning bright blue and white, and giving off red sparks.
The observation lasted for approximately 60 seconds.
The report concludes that the object could have been a meteor, an aircraft, or an astronomical phenomenon, but the cause is unknown.
sighted object: a falling object burning bright blue and white and giving off red sparks
